</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA13d187n1-ptr" id="PJA13d187n1">1</a>

   <p>See Mercy Otis Warrens response to this comment in her letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-13-02-0255" class="document">25 Oct.</a>, below. Presumably to insure that she did give adequate treatment to his Dutch negotiations, <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> enclosed his <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams, comp., &lt;i&gt;A Collection of State-Papers, Relative to the First Acknowledgment of the Sovereignity of the United States of America, and the Reception of Their Minister Plenipotentiary, by Their High-Mightinesses the States-General of the United Netherlands&lt;/i&gt;, The Hague, 1782. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Collection of State-Papers</span></span> with this letter (from James Warren, 1 Nov., <span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Letters Warren-Adams Letters: Being Chiefly a Correspondence among John Adams, Samuel Adams, and James Warren&lt;/i&gt; (Massachusetts Historical Society, &lt;i&gt;Collections&lt;/i&gt;, vols. 7273), Boston, 19171925; 2 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Warren-Adams Letters</span></span>, 2:181183).</p>

